Earthquake spent the last few days with us and I enjoyed spending time with him. He was a bottle baby after his mother died from complications during her c section. It was tragic and heartbreaking. Earthquake will always hold a special place in my heart for several reasons. Life is a precious gift from God and I’m so thankful for this life he has blessed me with. I give all the glory to God and his son Jesus Christ that died on the cross for us all and defeated death. Don’t forget the real reason for Easter Is to celebrate him and his sacrifice he made so we can live eternal life in heaven. ✝️ I have the most precious family and friends. I want to thank all of you for continuously showing my dogs so much love and support. 🫶🏼❤️ Big thanks to David and Christie for bringing Earthquake to hang out on the farm. Always love the fellowship with them. Stay safe and have a blessed rest of your week! 🫶🏼💜

Not dog related but too good not to post. Every time I post my horses on my story I normally receive a lot of sweet comments. I want to share with y’all how I got them. 

I purchased them both from a good friend of mine that recently passed away after a long hard battle with cancer. She was such a kind hearted person and loved horses and dogs just like I do. She actually had a puppy from my Tr🇺🇸mp X Jayla litter and he was so perfect for her. He was always by her side even on her hard days. She was so proud of her “pup pup” and she would often call me to tell me what he had done that day. 

I purchased the buckskin mare as a young foal and she is now 7 years old. I raised and trained her myself. She has turned into a fine ranch horse and is a pleasure to have around. I received the bay stud colt last summer as a 4 month old. He is in training and is turning into a big handsome boy.  They will always have green pastures to call home here at Southern Elite and receive endless love and care.  They are my daily reminder of my good friend. 

#cancersucks #southernelite #aqha #buckskin

Welcome to 🏆🥇 Southern Elite Kennelz🥇🏆

Southern Elite is tucked away in rural Mississippi. We raise world renowned XL American Bullies and European Dobermans. Our breeding stock has been carefully hand selected.
